replies.body:
> [{quoted}](name=Automated Riven,realm=NA,application-id=6kFXY1kR,discussion-id=6JWHilrN,comment-id=0003000c,timestamp=2018-04-26T05:31:16.346+0000)
>
> Thank you. &lt;3 All this &#x27;riven should be ionian now&#x27; is making me sad. Noxus is way cooler.
> 
> *edit* I dont know if you know anything about this. But since your one of the writers I am gonna ask anyhow. I was gonna make a thread but I am gonna throw it all in here. 
> 
> 
> Is there any way you can tell me why this paragraph got retconned?
> 
> This was my favorite part of rivens old lore because it spoke of her drive and it made her character make sense. In the new lore it states it like so. 
> 
> I feel ... I dont know how to explain... disconected from the new lore. I cant help but associate riven with the prior lore because this line &#x27;on a quest to seek atonement and a way to save the pure Noxian vision in which she believed.&#x27; makes her entire character make sense. Its why she shattered the sword, and also why she keeps it. Its why she refuses to go back, but it also drives her. Before she seemed to have a purpose and a reason to fight. Its frustrating to me that now all she wants (between the lore and the color story) to do is die. It doesnt make sense with some of her quotes. 
> &#x27;what is broken can be restored&#x27;
> &quot;Learn from your mistakes.&quot;
> &quot;My spirit is not lost.&quot;
> 
> and also the general theme between her passive movement quotes and the quotes which she says while her ult is active and the sword is symbolically and literally restored. 
> She talks alot about redemption (or at least thats the theme in her quotes) throughout the game and I feel like this lore is largely missing, or failing to capture, that entire aspect of her character. 
> 
> In case you didnt know some of her quote without ult active are these
>   &quot;So long I&#x27;ve wandered... &quot;
>   &quot;How should I proceed?&quot;
>   &quot;My spirit is not lost.&quot;
>   &quot;Burdens of the past.&quot;
>   &quot;What conflict awaits?&quot;
>   &quot;Choose your own path.&quot;
>   &quot;My hands are stained.&quot;
>   &quot;Learn from your mistakes.&quot;
>   &quot;A sword mirrors its owner.&quot;
> 
> and with ult they change to these. 
>   &quot;I know my purpose.&quot;
>   &quot;A moment of clarity.&quot;
>   &quot;Leave doubt behind.&quot;
>   &quot;No more hesitation.&quot;
>   &quot;No looking back.&quot;
> 
> I feel like none of these quotes fit her new lore very well. 
> 
> Anyhow. sorry to rant at you a bit. Any insight you could bestow would be appreciated.


I give you a hard agree right there. New Lore seemed to gloss over the very details I felt made Riven a compelling character to begin with. I would like to at least see_ some_ of this restored to her new lore - maybe address questions of how she can both atone for her past while also believing Noxus is redeemable, you know? If her new theme is anything to go by, why stop at just redeeming herself?
